               <msContents>
                  <summary>Notification of the death of a slave, Apollophanes, a weaver, by his master Sarapion. The notification is addressed to Philiskos, a tax farmer for the tax on weaving.  Dated in the 7th year of Nero and signed by Philiskos</summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">Written along the fibers; on the verso, 4 lines, effaced.  The first line is probably the name Philiskos</note>
                     <note type="general">22 lines; broken at right and bottom left corner.  Only 1-2 letters are missing at the right</note>
                     <note type="general">The hand is a fine, fluent cursive</note>
                     <note type="general">The last 4 lines are in the hand of Philiskos, thickly written</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">In Greek</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
